5
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:16,960
How did Pauline answer the telephone at 9 o'clock?

6
00:00:19,079 --> 00:00:22,239
What's Ron Maaston like, Pauline?

7
00:00:22,339 --> 00:00:25,100
He's awful.

8
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:32,159
He telephone me four times yesterday and three times the day before yesterday.

9
00:00:32,759 --> 00:00:38,640
He telephone the office yesterday morning and yesterday afternoon.

10
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:41,739
My boss answered the telephone.

11
00:00:43,020 --> 00:00:45,279
What did your boss say to him?

12
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:49,739
He said, Pauline is typing letters.

13
00:00:50,140 --> 00:00:52,199
She can't speak to you now.

14
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:56,919
Then I arrived home at six o'clock yesterday evening.

15
00:00:57,359 --> 00:00:58,779
He telephoned again.

16
00:00:59,439 --> 00:01:01,599
But I didn't answer the phone.

17
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,859
Did he telephone again last night?

18
00:01:05,780 --> 00:01:06,920
Yes, he did.

19
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:09,959
He telephoned at 9 o'clock.

20
00:01:10,939 --> 00:01:13,019
What did you say to him?

21
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:17,019
I said, this is Pauline's mother.

22
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:20,319
Please don't telephone my daughter again.

23
00:01:21,159 --> 00:01:22,739
Did he telephone again?

24
00:01:23,359 --> 00:01:24,980
No, he didn't.

25
00:01:39,659 --> 00:01:42,140
Thank you.

